cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with machine learning techniques for 6-DoF localization of monocular images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is evaluated on real-world autonomous driving and indoor localization datasets, which suggests that it could also fall under robotics (cs.RO). The use of recurrent models and probabilistic pose estimates indicates a focus on deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation on video datasets suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
